service.tut.pori.contentanalysis

Class MediaObjectList

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.tut.pori.http.ResponseData
      • service.tut.pori.contentanalysis.MediaObjectList

  • public class MediaObjectList
extends ResponseData
    A list of media objects, which can be directly used as a data for XML response.

    XML Example

    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<objectList>
  <object>
    <backendId>1414580432</backendId>
    <confidence>0.4795504924398071</confidence>
    <mediaObjectId>3097483530515870851</mediaObjectId>
    <mediaType>PHOTO</mediaType>
    <objectId>vhNHoQPNmyAQFcSSKgIlEJquoyBhMselfEcHoatgkyVsWOveMyERYtFmNRplQWWV</objectId>
    <rank>1575870776</rank>
    <serviceId>1</serviceId>
    <status>NO_FRIENDLY_KEYWORD</status>
    <objectType>KEYWORD</objectType>
    <value>HmSLoyeLEWsFMzGMqNbiwIIUSgCzbDbvgFsDhvnzFawwiWQoxKDjhvKLlFyefXIK</value>
    <visibility>GROUP</visibility>
    <userId>1029302779899766414</userId>
  </object>
</objectList>
    See Also:
    MediaObject

      • getMediaObjectListFromKeywords

        public static MediaObjectList getMediaObjectListFromKeywords(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keywords)

        Parse given keywords given in following format:

        keyword:confidence:backendId,keyword:confidence:backendId,...

        keyword is required, confidence and backendId are optional.

        Parameters:
        keywords -
        Returns:
        list of media objects based on the keywords or null if none was found
